@page "/player/wishlist"
@attribute [Authorize]

<PageTitle>Wishlist</PageTitle>

<section class="space-y-6">
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-4 lg:flex-row lg:items-end lg:justify-between">
        <div>
            <h1 class="mt-4 app-page-title">Wishlist</h1>
            <p class="mt-4 max-w-3xl text-base leading-8 text-slate-300">
                Wishlist management is reserved now as a signed-in player route. The add and remove actions from the game library will arrive in a future backend wave.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-3 sm:flex-row">
            <a class="rounded-full bg-cyan-300 px-5 py-3 text-center text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-950" href="/games">Browse Games</a>
            <a class="rounded-full border border-white/15 px-5 py-3 text-center text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-100" href="/player/games">Back to my games</a>
        </div>
    </div>

    <section class="app-panel p-6">
        <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.22em] text-cyan-100/70">Future wishlist API</div>
        <h2 class="mt-3 text-2xl font-semibold text-white">No wishlist items yet</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 max-w-3xl text-sm leading-7 text-slate-300">
            This placeholder route will become the private home for titles a player wants to track before purchase. Game library cards and title detail pages will eventually add wishlist actions that write to this view.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="grid gap-4 lg:grid-cols-3">
        <section class="app-panel p-6">
            <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.22em] text-cyan-100/70">Add from browse</div>
            <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-7 text-slate-300">
                Signed-in users will be able to add titles from the game library without leaving the library browse experience.
            </p>
        </section>
        <section class="app-panel p-6">
            <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.22em] text-cyan-100/70">Private list</div>
            <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-7 text-slate-300">
                Wishlist entries remain private to the authenticated player and do not change the public storefront.
            </p>
        </section>
        <section class="app-panel p-6">
            <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.22em] text-cyan-100/70">Later integration</div>
            <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-7 text-slate-300">
                Wishlist items can later inform notifications, collection seeding, and ownership conversion once commerce arrives.
            </p>
        </section>
    </section>
</section>
